823
00:49:34,262 --> 00:49:35,597
Let's try.

824
00:49:37,307 --> 00:49:39,768
Because I was let go unexpectedly,

825
00:49:39,851 --> 00:49:43,939
my family had to suffer and accept
the fact that I am now jobless.

826
00:49:44,022 --> 00:49:46,858
We lost our jobs
through no fault of our own.

827
00:49:46,942 --> 00:49:48,443
The company wasn't even struggling.

828
00:49:48,527 --> 00:49:50,362
Just to ensure the CEO's

829
00:49:50,445 --> 00:49:51,905
-selfish gain...
-Good day.

830
00:49:52,322 --> 00:49:53,949
-You can't go in.
-Don't worry. It's fine.

831
00:49:54,032 --> 00:49:54,866
It's okay.

832
00:49:56,118 --> 00:49:58,662
-Our families--
-How do you do?

833
00:49:58,745 --> 00:50:00,038
This must be exhausting.

834
00:50:00,122 --> 00:50:03,166
Hello, I'm Mr. Song Hui-seop.

835
00:50:04,459 --> 00:50:06,878
Listen. Do you think
this will help you resolve the issue?

836
00:50:07,004 --> 00:50:10,007
I'm well aware
of the situation you are in.

837
00:50:10,090 --> 00:50:11,550
Let's talk it out

838
00:50:11,633 --> 00:50:14,136
and try to get to the bottom of the issue.

839
00:50:14,219 --> 00:50:15,053
Yes.

840
00:50:16,304 --> 00:50:20,017
Jeez, this pack of worthless riffraff
always wants something more.

841
00:50:20,100 --> 00:50:22,352
Must they throw a fit like this?
What a headache.

842
00:50:22,436 --> 00:50:23,729
These bastards, seriously.

843
00:50:23,812 --> 00:50:25,313
What did you just say?

844
00:50:25,605 --> 00:50:26,898
-What did he say?
-What?

845
00:50:29,484 --> 00:50:31,987
You worthless riffraff.

846
00:50:33,238 --> 00:50:35,323
-You piece of--
-You can't do this!

847
00:50:35,407 --> 00:50:37,242
-Oh, gosh.
-How dare you!

848
00:50:37,325 --> 00:50:39,411
-Hey!
-What the heck did you say?

849
00:50:39,494 --> 00:50:41,872
-Please don't be like this.
-You bastard!

850
00:50:41,955 --> 00:50:43,665
-Gosh, no!
-Go to hell!

851
00:50:43,749 --> 00:50:45,292
-Get a taste of this!
-You prick!

852
00:50:45,375 --> 00:50:47,210
-Don't do this, please.
-Get back here!

853
00:50:47,294 --> 00:50:49,463
The Judiciary Committee
hearing was adjourned,

854
00:50:49,546 --> 00:50:51,381
and protesters who were criticizing it

855
00:50:51,465 --> 00:50:54,843
attacked Assemblyman Song Hui-seop
earlier today.

856
00:50:54,926 --> 00:50:58,472
This left Mr. Song injured,
and he requires three weeks of treatment.

857
00:50:58,555 --> 00:51:00,724
The member of Bugang's labor union
who led the attack

858
00:51:00,807 --> 00:51:02,559
was arrested on site.

859
00:51:02,726 --> 00:51:04,352
Just a moment. Let go.

860
00:51:06,772 --> 00:51:09,316
This certainly isn't their fault.

861
00:51:09,399 --> 00:51:12,194
It's all because of the crippled operation
of the National Assembly.

862
00:51:12,277 --> 00:51:13,779
Once the inspection resumes,

863
00:51:13,862 --> 00:51:16,740
I will wholeheartedly listen
to their issues and concerns

864
00:51:16,823 --> 00:51:19,785
and do my best to find a solution.

865
00:51:22,037 --> 00:51:25,957
Also, I have no interest
in taking legal action against them.

866
00:51:26,208 --> 00:51:30,587
I ask the police to be lenient with them.

867
00:51:30,670 --> 00:51:31,713
Please let us through.

868
00:51:31,922 --> 00:51:33,590
Are you really not going to press charges?

869
00:51:33,673 --> 00:51:34,883
Are you really all right, sir?

870
00:51:34,966 --> 00:51:36,968
-How's the injury, sir?
-Oh, my...

871
00:51:37,052 --> 00:51:39,387
-Gosh, sir.
-Are you okay, sir?

872
00:51:40,222 --> 00:51:41,848
I'm okay. Let's go.

873
00:51:41,932 --> 00:51:43,100
-How's the wound?
-It's fine.

874
00:51:43,183 --> 00:51:44,518
-Let us through.
-Are you sure?

875
00:51:44,601 --> 00:51:46,436
-Sir.
-Please say a few words.

876
00:51:49,689 --> 00:51:50,982
Are you all right, sir?

877
00:51:52,859 --> 00:51:55,821
Getting beaten up like this
is part of maturing as a politician.

878
00:51:58,031 --> 00:51:59,783
What do you think?
This'll be enough, right?

879
00:51:59,866 --> 00:52:00,992
Yes, sir.

880
00:52:02,077 --> 00:52:04,704
-Hey, let go. It's hot.
-Yes, sir.

881
00:52:07,791 --> 00:52:09,042
Any ideas?

882
00:52:11,753 --> 00:52:13,380
They're pushing ahead with it

883
00:52:13,713 --> 00:52:15,298
because they can justify it.

884
00:52:15,382 --> 00:52:18,426
You should use it too, sir.

885
00:52:18,802 --> 00:52:21,012
Politicians are always
most afraid of public opinion.

886
00:52:29,855 --> 00:52:32,107
Jeez, this foul stench. It stinks.

887
00:52:32,691 --> 00:52:34,985
-Goodness. Hey, hold my arm.
-Pardon me?

888
00:52:35,068 --> 00:52:37,320
-Hold my arm. We're getting off.
-Yes, sir.

889
00:52:37,863 --> 00:52:39,156
Oh, boy. This is killing me.

890
00:52:43,451 --> 00:52:44,661
-Sir.
-Sir.

891
00:52:44,744 --> 00:52:46,621
-Are you all right, sir?
-Yes, I'm fine.

892
00:52:46,705 --> 00:52:48,290
-Are you okay?
-Yes, I'm okay.

893
00:52:48,373 --> 00:52:50,125
-Really?
-Stop it. There are many people here.

894
00:52:50,208 --> 00:52:52,878
-Still, are you sure you'll be okay?
-Hello, good day.

895
00:52:53,378 --> 00:52:54,754
Yes, hello. Goodness!

896
00:52:59,259 --> 00:53:00,510
Are you all right, sir?

897
00:53:00,594 --> 00:53:02,053
CHIEF OF
CENTRAL DISTRICT PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

898
00:53:09,853 --> 00:53:11,146
NO SEUNG-JIN

899
00:53:16,651 --> 00:53:18,361
Aren't we going to get started?

900
00:53:29,748 --> 00:53:31,124
We'll resume the hearing.

901
00:53:37,422 --> 00:53:40,717
Ms. Kang, why bring up issues
that weren't discussed beforehand?

902
00:53:40,800 --> 00:53:41,760
I apologize, sir.

903
00:53:43,053 --> 00:53:44,179
I'll stop there.

904
00:53:45,555 --> 00:53:47,766
Mr. Lee Seong-min, you may ask questions.

905
00:53:48,516 --> 00:53:49,434
Sure.

906
00:53:50,101 --> 00:53:51,478
Minister of Employment and Labor,

907
00:53:51,561 --> 00:53:53,688
regarding Bugang Electronics'
subcontractors--

908
00:53:53,772 --> 00:53:56,942
Mr. Lee, you're repeating
what Ms. Kang was doing earlier.

909
00:53:57,025 --> 00:53:58,693
That wasn't agreed upon beforehand.

910
00:53:58,777 --> 00:54:01,238
Well, I think this is an important issue.

911
00:54:01,321 --> 00:54:05,200
Sir, you know of a company
called Hyeonmi Hitech, right?

912
00:54:05,283 --> 00:54:06,117
Yes, I do.

913
00:54:07,035 --> 00:54:11,289
Hyeonmi Hitech is
one of Bugang's major suppliers.

914
00:54:11,373 --> 00:54:13,667
According to this,
your son, Jo Hyeong-tae,

915
00:54:13,750 --> 00:54:15,669
currently works there.

916
00:54:16,503 --> 00:54:18,964
You keep interrupting
every time the issue is brought up.

917
00:54:19,047 --> 00:54:20,590
If it's because of this--

918
00:54:20,674 --> 00:54:23,009
My son isn't even a permanent employee.

919
00:54:23,093 --> 00:54:26,012
He's just working under a contract.
Please watch what you say.

920
00:54:26,096 --> 00:54:29,891
I brought it up as I was concerned
that the people might view it that way.

921
00:54:29,975 --> 00:54:32,644
Since your son also has
a contract position,

922
00:54:32,727 --> 00:54:36,898
I'm sure you understand
the importance of this issue.

923
00:54:36,982 --> 00:54:41,152
I say that because most of the
dispatched workers are contract employees.

924
00:54:42,654 --> 00:54:46,449
Well, may I continue on this topic?

925
00:54:50,078 --> 00:54:50,954
Yes, continue.

926
00:54:51,037 --> 00:54:52,330
Thank you.

927
00:54:54,749 --> 00:54:57,836
Minister. Among Bugang Electronics'
30 workers that lost their lives,

928
00:54:57,919 --> 00:55:00,505
including Kim Gwang-hun
who died a few days ago,

929
00:55:00,588 --> 00:55:03,383
twenty-nine of them were subcontractors.
You're aware of that, right?

930
00:55:03,550 --> 00:55:05,885
However, Bugang held their subcontractors

931
00:55:05,969 --> 00:55:07,387
responsible for their deaths.

932
00:55:07,470 --> 00:55:09,389
And then, with their zero-accident record,

933
00:55:09,472 --> 00:55:12,017
they got a 21 billion won reduction
from their insurance.

934
00:55:12,100 --> 00:55:14,769
But what Bugang owes
for unpaid wages and pension contributions

935
00:55:14,853 --> 00:55:18,356
as well as for the compulsory insurances
amounts to 17 billion won.

936
00:55:18,440 --> 00:55:19,774
Does this make sense to you?

937
00:55:20,942 --> 00:55:22,986
-I'll take care of it.
-Among all the OECD countries,

938
00:55:23,069 --> 00:55:25,071
Korea has the highest
occupational fatality rate.

939
00:55:25,155 --> 00:55:26,990
It's been that way for the past 21 years.

940
00:55:27,073 --> 00:55:30,201
Workplace accidents have been killing
5 workers a day, 2,000 workers a year.

941
00:55:30,327 --> 00:55:32,162
We must pass a bill
for workplace fatalities

942
00:55:32,245 --> 00:55:34,831
and establish a separate agency
for occupational safety and health.

943
00:55:34,914 --> 00:55:36,333
What are your thoughts on this?

944
00:55:37,625 --> 00:55:38,626
Mr. Lee.

945
00:55:41,046 --> 00:55:43,131
-What is this?
-We received...

946
00:55:43,214 --> 00:55:44,507
Well...

947
00:55:44,591 --> 00:55:47,385
My office received an anonymous tip.

948
00:55:47,469 --> 00:55:50,138
The occupational health
and safety inspection on Bugang

949
00:55:50,221 --> 00:55:52,223
revealed that 81 percent
of Bugang's labor agencies

950
00:55:52,307 --> 00:55:56,478
utilized flextime illegally without
obtaining permission from the workers.

951
00:55:56,770 --> 00:55:59,522
Why didn't you submit this report?

952
00:56:02,650 --> 00:56:03,485
That's--

953
00:56:03,568 --> 00:56:06,404
Laborers who work over 10 hours a day
more than twice a week are 2.7 times

954
00:56:06,488 --> 00:56:08,615
more likely to have depression
and anxiety disorders.

955
00:56:08,698 --> 00:56:11,034
Risks of MI tripled
and for diabetes it quadrupled

956
00:56:11,117 --> 00:56:12,410
when working over 11 hours.

957
00:56:12,494 --> 00:56:14,704
Kim Gwang-hun, who worked with Bugang,
also suffered from

958
00:56:14,788 --> 00:56:17,874
anxiety disorder and myocardial infarction
before his death.

959
00:56:17,957 --> 00:56:18,792
Minister.

960
00:56:21,378 --> 00:56:23,213
Do you really think Mr. Kim
took his own life?

961
00:56:23,296 --> 00:56:24,464
Tell me what you think.

962
00:56:25,548 --> 00:56:30,428
I think Bugang practically murdered him!

963
00:56:30,512 --> 00:56:31,846
Answer my question!

964
00:56:33,473 --> 00:56:35,141
We must investigate Bugang Electronics'

965
00:56:35,225 --> 00:56:38,019
working environment thoroughly
and as soon as possible

966
00:56:38,103 --> 00:56:39,104
and make improvements.

967
00:56:39,771 --> 00:56:43,942
Also, all workers who were dismissed
wrongfully must be reinstated immediately.

968
00:56:44,567 --> 00:56:45,735
Minister.

969
00:56:46,569 --> 00:56:48,988
Please make sure it's done.
I'll be watching you.

970
00:56:51,950 --> 00:56:53,451
Bugang Electronics' CEO, Mr. Kim.

971
00:56:54,119 --> 00:56:56,579
Did you have lunch? What did you eat?

972
00:56:57,080 --> 00:56:58,623
I brought lunch from home.

973
00:56:59,707 --> 00:57:00,834
Did you enjoy your lunch?

974
00:57:00,917 --> 00:57:02,085
Mr. Kim!

975
00:57:02,585 --> 00:57:05,046
How could you eat anything

976
00:57:05,130 --> 00:57:06,256
after firing so many workers?

977
00:57:06,756 --> 00:57:10,885
Just hearing about it makes me emotional!

978
00:57:10,969 --> 00:57:12,429
How can you even think about food?

979
00:57:13,179 --> 00:57:15,849
Also, Chief of the Central District
Prosecutors' Office.

980
00:57:16,599 --> 00:57:19,394
You are supposedly assisting
the Minister of Justice

981
00:57:19,477 --> 00:57:21,729
in his efforts to reform the prosecution.

982
00:57:21,813 --> 00:57:24,107
How could you conspire with corporations?

983
00:57:24,190 --> 00:57:26,526
You let things slide
and even delayed their indictment.

984
00:57:26,609 --> 00:57:29,195
What's more? The prosecution is actively

985
00:57:29,279 --> 00:57:31,781
trying to dismantle labor unions.

986
00:57:31,865 --> 00:57:34,242
Is that the prosecution's job?
How could you explain this?

987
00:57:34,367 --> 00:57:35,243
Answer my question.

988
00:57:36,244 --> 00:57:37,954
Is that the prosecution's job?

989
00:57:38,329 --> 00:57:39,539
Is it?

990
00:57:40,039 --> 00:57:41,958
How could the prosecution do such things?

991
00:57:42,041 --> 00:57:43,710
Do you think it's acceptable?

992
00:57:46,045 --> 00:57:48,131
-Please make a comment.
-Thank you. Good work.

993
00:57:48,214 --> 00:57:51,217
-Thank you all.
-Most importantly, I think all members

994
00:57:51,301 --> 00:57:55,346
of the Assembly need to know
how much the workers are suffering.

995
00:57:56,556 --> 00:57:57,891
I kept my promise,

996
00:57:57,974 --> 00:57:59,726
so it's now your turn to keep your word.

997
00:57:59,809 --> 00:58:03,062
The spokesperson position of
the Daehan Party will always be yours.

998
00:58:05,648 --> 00:58:07,358
Is your son really working there?

999
00:58:07,442 --> 00:58:09,194
We won't be accepting any questions.

1000
00:58:09,277 --> 00:58:11,571
-I'm sorry.
-Move back, please.

1001
00:58:12,155 --> 00:58:13,156
Excuse me for a second.

1002
00:58:13,364 --> 00:58:15,158
-When did your son start...
-Mr. Jo!

1003
00:58:15,241 --> 00:58:16,951
-Please say a few words.
-Mr. Jo.

1004
00:58:17,035 --> 00:58:19,746
Did you cut some sort of deal
with my boss?

1005
00:58:20,914 --> 00:58:21,789
I'll tell you later.

1006
00:58:23,208 --> 00:58:24,501
Good work today, Mr. Jang.

1007
00:58:24,584 --> 00:58:26,878
Oh, thank you. Well done today.

1008
00:58:26,961 --> 00:58:29,255
Once we reach an agreement,

1009
00:58:29,339 --> 00:58:32,258
we'll hand it over
to the Judiciary Committee.

1010
00:58:32,342 --> 00:58:34,511
But what's more important

1011
00:58:35,220 --> 00:58:39,390
is thinking about what a worker's
lonely death means to our society and...

1012
00:58:39,474 --> 00:58:40,850
The CEO of Bugang Electronics,

1013
00:58:40,934 --> 00:58:43,770
Mr. Kim Hyeon-su, attended
the first hearing today as a witness.

1014
00:58:43,853 --> 00:58:47,106
The Judiciary Committee...

1015
00:58:47,190 --> 00:58:49,108
Why are you celebrating all alone here?

1016
00:58:49,192 --> 00:58:50,902
You totally stole the limelight today.

1017
00:58:52,070 --> 00:58:53,696
The limelight, my ass.

1018
00:58:54,739 --> 00:58:55,949
It wasn't all me.

1019
00:58:56,032 --> 00:58:57,867
Ms. Kang helped me.

1020
00:59:01,162 --> 00:59:02,956
Drink soju instead.

1021
00:59:09,921 --> 00:59:11,839
Ms. Kang gave me this.

1022
00:59:11,923 --> 00:59:13,174
LIST OF QUESTIONS

1023
00:59:14,384 --> 00:59:18,846
And someone mailed this to my office,
but there's no name or address.

1024
00:59:18,930 --> 00:59:20,890
You wrote this, didn't you?

1025
00:59:22,058 --> 00:59:23,434
My job is keeping me busy enough.

1026
00:59:23,518 --> 00:59:26,396
Why would I be concerned with your job?

1027
00:59:27,272 --> 00:59:30,400
I taught you how to write these
when you were still wet behind the ears.

1028
00:59:30,483 --> 00:59:31,651
I'd obviously...

1029
00:59:32,360 --> 00:59:34,028
recognize questionnaires written by you.

1030
00:59:34,112 --> 00:59:36,948
Because Assemblyman Song Hui-seop
brought up Bugang workers'

1031
00:59:37,031 --> 00:59:38,366
wrongful dismissal lawsuit,

1032
00:59:38,449 --> 00:59:41,578
the bill for improving
occupational health and safety...

1033
00:59:41,661 --> 00:59:44,289
In order to do so,
the society needs to improve...

1034
00:59:44,497 --> 00:59:46,708
I'm still getting help from you.

1035
00:59:46,791 --> 00:59:49,252
You'll be a much better assemblyman
than I am.

1036
00:59:50,336 --> 00:59:51,462
Tae-jun.

1037
00:59:52,005 --> 00:59:55,717
Please... Just don't turn out
like your boss, Mr. Song.

1038
00:59:55,800 --> 01:00:00,013
Don't worry about me.
You should worry about yourself.

1039
01:00:00,513 --> 01:00:01,973
Try to be a little ambitious, please.

1040
01:00:02,056 --> 01:00:04,684
Don't get fixated on a single issue.

1041
01:00:04,767 --> 01:00:07,478
-Don't you want to be reelected next year?
-Come on.

1042
01:00:08,187 --> 01:00:10,857
I should be satisfied
with being elected once.

1043
01:00:10,940 --> 01:00:12,734
I'm exhausted. I can't do this anymore.

1044
01:00:15,236 --> 01:00:17,947
Oh, how about I work
as your chief of staff

1045
01:00:18,031 --> 01:00:19,282
when you get elected?

1046
01:00:19,699 --> 01:00:22,076
Who'd hire an old man like you
as their chief of staff?

1047
01:00:22,368 --> 01:00:26,122
So you won't even consider hiring me
because I'm old. My goodness.

1048
01:00:30,168 --> 01:00:31,628
HUMAN RIGHTS COMMITTEE DIRECTOR

1049
01:00:33,504 --> 01:00:36,758
Hi, my dear daughter.
No, I'm not drinking.

1050
01:00:36,841 --> 01:00:39,093
I'm on my way home now.

1051
01:00:39,177 --> 01:00:41,346
Did you see me on the news?

1052
01:00:42,388 --> 01:00:44,474
I'll be home shortly. All right.

1053
01:00:45,141 --> 01:00:47,685
Hey, you came too late.
I have to go home now.

1054
01:00:47,769 --> 01:00:49,354
Drinks are on me, so finish them.

1055
01:00:49,437 --> 01:00:52,106
Excuse me. Please give him
whatever he asks for.

1056
01:00:52,190 --> 01:00:54,359
I'll pay for everything
next time I'm here. Hey, I'm off.

1057
01:00:54,442 --> 01:00:57,028
You called me here.
How can you just leave?

1058
01:00:57,111 --> 01:00:58,613
Shall I pick up some fried chicken?

1059
01:00:59,113 --> 01:01:01,324
Yes, that one.

1060
01:01:11,209 --> 01:01:14,420
Assemblyman Lee Seong-min also raised
suspicions about the relationship

1061
01:01:14,504 --> 01:01:17,131
between Bugang and Daehan Party's
Assemblyman Jo Gap-yeong.

1062
01:01:17,465 --> 01:01:20,009
It has been revealed that
Mr. Jo's son, Mr. Jo Hyeong-tae,

1063
01:01:20,093 --> 01:01:24,430
currently works at Hyeonmi Hitech,
which is one of Bugang's suppliers,

1064
01:01:24,514 --> 01:01:28,393
and all eyes are on what stance
Mr. Jo will take regarding it.

1065
01:01:37,443 --> 01:01:40,530
Oh, my. You made it, Mr. Jang.

1066
01:01:41,030 --> 01:01:42,156
Here.

1067
01:01:42,824 --> 01:01:45,034
-How have you been, sir?
-Have a seat over there.

1068
01:01:45,118 --> 01:01:46,035
Yes, sit here.

1069
01:01:49,997 --> 01:01:52,417
Mr. Jang, excellent work today.

1070
01:01:52,500 --> 01:01:55,420
No, sir. It was all Mr. Song's idea.

1071
01:01:58,089 --> 01:02:00,383
This is why I like you.

1072
01:02:00,466 --> 01:02:02,260
You're very modest.

1073
01:02:03,177 --> 01:02:05,346
I want to give my hard-earned money
to my son.

1074
01:02:05,430 --> 01:02:07,765
Why do people have
so much to say about it?

1075
01:02:08,683 --> 01:02:11,602
Anyway, I'll never forget
all the help you've given me, Mr. Jang.

1076
01:02:11,728 --> 01:02:15,273
I'll help you to the best of my ability
so that you can wear

1077
01:02:15,356 --> 01:02:17,650
the assemblyman badge on your chest soon.

1078
01:02:18,818 --> 01:02:20,153
The food will get cold. Dig in.

1079
01:02:20,236 --> 01:02:21,446
-Yes, sir.
-Hey.

1080
01:02:22,029 --> 01:02:26,033
You made us come all the way here
from Seoul. Is this really it?

1081
01:02:27,994 --> 01:02:29,620
Of course not.

1082
01:02:29,704 --> 01:02:32,248
I prepared a full package.

1083
01:02:33,499 --> 01:02:34,709
All right, let's drink.

1084
01:02:34,792 --> 01:02:36,252
Okay. Cheers.

1085
01:02:38,254 --> 01:02:39,088
Well...

1086
01:02:39,672 --> 01:02:42,592
Do you know
Assemblyman Lee Seong-min well?

1087
01:02:44,719 --> 01:02:46,512
-Why do you ask?
-You see,

1088
01:02:46,596 --> 01:02:49,432
because he keeps going on about labor laws
and occupational regulations,

1089
01:02:49,515 --> 01:02:52,435
it's practically impossible
to run a business here in Seongjin.

1090
01:02:52,518 --> 01:02:54,437
You saw him acting up
at the hearing earlier.

1091
01:02:54,520 --> 01:02:56,939
If he keeps it up,
he'll cause so much headache for us.

1092
01:02:58,065 --> 01:03:01,819
Sir, is there anything you can do
to shut him up?

1093
01:03:01,903 --> 01:03:03,946
Don't mind him. He's just a small fry.

1094
01:03:04,614 --> 01:03:08,910
Goodness, I guess you have no idea.

1095
01:03:09,202 --> 01:03:12,997
Pricks like him are the ones
we must watch out for the most.

1096
01:03:13,080 --> 01:03:15,041
Those who utterly have nothing,
including ambition.

1097
01:03:18,586 --> 01:03:20,880
Look, Mr. Lee.

1098
01:03:25,009 --> 01:03:27,762
Oh, boy. I got all riled up
in front of you

1099
01:03:27,845 --> 01:03:29,680
because of a jerk who talks too much.

1100
01:03:29,806 --> 01:03:31,182
My apologies.

1101
01:03:33,267 --> 01:03:35,520
Here, let's drink.

1102
01:03:35,603 --> 01:03:37,104
-All right.
-Great.

1103
01:03:38,356 --> 01:03:39,273
You too, Mr. Jang.

1104
01:03:54,038 --> 01:03:55,873
This is your hometown, right?

1105
01:03:56,040 --> 01:03:57,041
Yes, sir.

1106
01:03:57,583 --> 01:03:59,001
The subway track runs through here.

1107
01:03:59,335 --> 01:04:00,711
It's a quaint little neighborhood.

1108
01:04:01,546 --> 01:04:03,714
When he asked me to come here for drinks,

1109
01:04:04,340 --> 01:04:06,008
I knew something was up.

1110
01:04:07,218 --> 01:04:08,177
That must be it.

1111
01:04:09,595 --> 01:04:10,805
OFFICE OF ASSEMBLYMAN LEE SEONG-MIN

1112
01:04:13,182 --> 01:04:15,268
I'll talk to Mr. Lee Seong-min.

1113
01:04:15,351 --> 01:04:17,395
No, it's okay. I'll take care of it.

1114
01:04:18,020 --> 01:04:20,231
Just focus on the inspection for now.

1115
01:04:20,314 --> 01:04:23,317
We have to hit the minister's head hard
on the last day.

1116
01:04:23,860 --> 01:04:25,152
Let's go.

1117
01:04:35,955 --> 01:04:38,708
OFFICE OF ASSEMBLYMAN LEE SEONG-MIN

1118
01:04:53,347 --> 01:04:54,307
Tae-jun.

1119
01:04:55,391 --> 01:04:57,852
-Did you see the news?
-The sign from Assemblyman Lee's

1120
01:04:57,935 --> 01:05:00,897
district office fell on a passerby,
resulting in a severe injury.

1121
01:05:00,980 --> 01:05:03,441
The victim of the accident,
who is a woman in her 40s,

1122
01:05:03,524 --> 01:05:06,986
was sent to a hospital nearby
and is now undergoing her second surgery.

1123
01:05:07,069 --> 01:05:09,947
The police are trying to find out
if the sign violated any...

1124
01:05:18,164 --> 01:05:19,165
Hello.

1125
01:05:23,002 --> 01:05:24,253
Which one is a latte?

1126
01:05:24,337 --> 01:05:26,464
Oh, the latte is for the chief of staff.

1127
01:05:26,547 --> 01:05:27,882
Mr. Jang doesn't drink latte.

1128
01:05:28,466 --> 01:05:29,467
No, the other one.

1129
01:05:29,550 --> 01:05:32,094
"The other one"? Who?

1130
01:05:32,178 --> 01:05:34,347
The police are investigating if the sign

1131
01:05:34,430 --> 01:05:37,266
violated any of the regulations
for signs and advertising devices.

1132
01:05:37,350 --> 01:05:40,353
Assemblyman Lee Seong-min expressed
his regret and visited the victim,

1133
01:05:40,436 --> 01:05:42,688
but the victim's family
refused to meet him.

1134
01:05:42,772 --> 01:05:45,566
Mr. Oh Won-sik is here
from the district office.

1135
01:05:46,943 --> 01:05:49,070
I'll try meeting
with Assemblyman Lee Seong-min.

1136
01:05:49,153 --> 01:05:51,614
No, it's okay. I'll take care of it.

1137
01:05:54,742 --> 01:05:56,953
Hey, you're here.

1138
01:06:29,986 --> 01:06:32,154
Mr. Oh Won-sik is here
from the district office.

1139
01:06:32,238 --> 01:06:34,824
-Hey, you're here.
-He was shunted off because of you.

1140
01:06:34,907 --> 01:06:36,033
He won't just sit still.

1141
01:06:36,117 --> 01:06:38,327
The inspection will probably end
like this. Can you catch him?

1142
01:06:38,411 --> 01:06:40,079
We can't give up now.

1143
01:06:40,162 --> 01:06:42,665
If there is something blocking my way,
I will jump over it.

1144
01:06:42,748 --> 01:06:44,709
There may be material
that hasn't been revealed.

1145
01:06:44,792 --> 01:06:46,585
-Any story will be of value to us.
-Yes, sir.

1146
01:06:46,669 --> 01:06:48,504
I think Tae-jun found something.

1147
01:06:48,587 --> 01:06:50,673
Were you behind the incident
regarding Mr. Lee?

1148
01:06:50,756 --> 01:06:52,758
Don't cross the line, Tae-jun.

1149
01:06:53,509 --> 01:06:55,511
You might get hurt.

1150
